100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 9, 1926, the League of Nations convened for discussions on disarmament, emphasizing global efforts to prevent future conflicts. In the United States, the Senate continued debates on the controversial McNary-Haugen Bill aimed at supporting struggling farmers. Meanwhile, in Italy, Mussolini's government intensified its crackdown on dissent, further consolidating power amid rising tensions in Europe.
